    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix potential array out-of-bounds access in get_next_ue_initial_id()\n\n### Summary\nThe `get_next_ue_initial_id()` function in `rrc_eNB_S1AP.c` could potentially access memory outside its static array bounds when called with invalid `mod_id` values. Since `module_id_t` is a `uint16_t` but the array size is only `NUMBER_OF_eNB_MAX` (which is 1), passing any `mod_id >= 1` would cause out-of-bounds access.\n\nThis fix adds proper boundary checking and initialization to prevent this issue.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/RRC/LTE/rrc_eNB_S1AP.c`: Added boundary checking to prevent array access out of bounds\n- `openair2/RRC/LTE/rrc_eNB_S1AP.c`: Added explicit initialization of the static array\n- `openair2/RRC/LTE/rrc_eNB_S1AP.c`: Added error logging for invalid inputs\n\n### Reproduction\nTo reproduce the original issue:\n1. Call `get_next_ue_initial_id()` with `mod_id` value >= `NUMBER_OF_eNB_MAX` (i.e., >= 1)\n2. Observe potential memory corruption or undefined behavior due to out-of-bounds array access\n3. In some cases this could lead to segmentation faults or incorrect UE initial ID generation\n\nThe fix ensures that invalid `mod_id` values are properly handled with error logging and return of the invalid ID constant.\n"
}